The loading of CO2 molecules onto the surface was assured by emergence of a tiny M-CO3 peak in C 1s XPS (Supplementary Fig. 12d), suggesting the successful bonding of CO2 molecules to metallic sites. To probe how Mn ions could assist activation of CO2 molecules during the PR process, we calculated the average oxidation states (AOS) of Mn under test according to the following equation65:1AOS=8.95−1.13ΔS\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
